            "receipt_content_id": "1390",
            "receipt_content": {
              "receipt_content_id": 1390,
              "content": "Thank you for joining the City of San Diego municipal golf resident program! We appreciate your passion for golf and look forward to providing you with a high-quality golf experience.\n\nParticipation in the resident program entitles you to the following benefits: Receive special Resident rates at all three City of San Diego municipal courses; Book Resident tee times at Torrey Pines, Balboa Park and Mission Bay golf courses up to seven (7) days in advance of play with no charge using the City\u2019s online reservation system;  Book Resident tee times at Torrey Pines Golf Course, eight (8) to ninety (90) days in advance of play and pay a non-refundable Resident booking fee using the City\u2019s online reservation system. (Booking fees are charged to help maintain the integrity of the tee sheet and are paid at the time of your reservation. They are not applied to your green fees on your day of play). In the event you lose your card, you can purchase a new one for a $5 replacement fee at any City of San Diego golf facility. \n\nAs part of your participation in the Resident Program, new and existing members are expected to comply with some easy to follow requirements:\n\nIn order to receive Resident rates for your round, you MUST present your valid Resident I.D. Card to the staff when paying for green fees or monthly ticket fees. Members who are unable to present their existing card will be asked to pay the non-resident rate or may purchase a new card for a $5 replacement fee upon verification that they are members in the program.\n\nAll Resident card holders must be present at the time of check-in and may not reserve tee times on behalf of other players if they are not expecting to play.\n\nThe Resident ID card is considered the property of the City of San Diego and will be surrendered to a golf course official: (a) if used illegally in any manner, (b) if card holder fails to comply with course rules and regulations.\n\nThe Resident ID card is non-refundable and non-transferable.  Any Misuse of the Resident ID card may result in its forfeiture. \n\nThank you again for purchasing your annual resident card and we hope to see you often!\n\nCity of San Diego Golf Division\n",
              "signature_line": false,
              "separate_receipt": true,
              "allow_duplicates": true
            },
            "force_tax": null,
            "is_service_fee": "0",
            "parent_item_percent": null,
            "whichever_is": null,
            "service_fee_id": null,
            "button_color": null,
            "menu_category": null,
            "menu_subcategory": null,
            "soup_or_salad": "none",
            "resident_requirement": "1",
            "online_purchasing": "1",
            "online_terms": "WELCOME!\nThank you for joining the City of San Diego municipal golf resident program! We appreciate your passion for golf and look forward to providing you with a high-quality golf experience.\n\nIf this is your first time in the program, you will need to pick up your resident ID card at any one of our City of San Diego golf facilities (Balboa Park, Mission Bay or Torrey Pines) during your next visit. When you arrive, just let staff know you need to pick up your resident ID card and they will confirm your identity, take your photograph to help better protect your account from fraud, and issue your card. \n\nIf you are renewing in the program, your existing resident ID card will remain valid and you can continue to enjoy resident rates and tee times with no need to pick up a new card. \n\nParticipation in the resident program entitles you to the following benefits:\n\u2022\tReceive special Resident rates at all three City of San Diego municipal courses. \n\u2022\tBook Resident tee times at Torrey Pines, Balboa Park and Mission Bay golf courses up to seven (7) days in advance of play with no charge using the City\u2019s online reservation system.\n\u2022\tBook Resident tee times at Torrey Pines Golf Course, eight (8) to 90 days in advance of play and pay a non-refundable Resident booking fee using the City\u2019s online reservation system. Booking fees are charged to help maintain the integrity of the tee sheet and are paid at the time of your reservation. They are not applied to your green fees on your day of play. Booking fees are non-refundable. Any chargebacks related to online booking will be considered a violation of the City of San Diego municipal golf resident program booking policy and will result in immediate suspension of resident privileges. \nIn the event you lose your card, you can purchase a new one for a $5 replacement fee at any City of San Diego golf facility. \n\nAs part of your participation in the Resident Program, new and existing members are expected to comply with some easy-to-follow requirements:\n\u2022\tIn order to receive Resident rates for your round, you MUST present your valid Resident I.D. Card to the staff when paying for green fees or monthly ticket fees. Members who are unable to present their existing card will be asked to pay the non-resident rate or may purchase a new card for a $5 replacement fee upon verification that they are members in the program.\n\u2022\tAll Resident cardholders must be present at the time of check-in and may not reserve tee times on behalf of other players if they are not expecting to play.\n\u2022\tThe Resident ID card is considered the property of the City of San Diego and will be surrendered to a golf course official: (a) if used illegally in any manner, (b) if the cardholder fails to comply with course rules and regulations.\n\u2022\tThe Resident ID card is non-refundable and non-transferable.\n\n\nIf you have any questions about the City\u2019s municipal golf resident program, our Golf Division staff is happy to assist. Please call us at (858) 552-1662 Monday \u2013 Friday from 9 a.m. \u2013 3 p.m.\n\nThank you again for purchasing your annual resident card and we hope to see you often!\n\nCity of San Diego Golf Division\n",
